@1001QAdotNET My logic would be to read the channel. If I detect the '--More--' string, then I keep reading.

If I detect the trailing prompt, then I stop reading.

So in psuedo-code, something like:

```
while True:
    new_data = net_connect.read_channel()
    output += new_data                       # record everything that has been received
    if '--More--' in new_data:
        net_connect.write_channel(' ')   # Send space character down the channel
        time.sleep(1)
    elif 'Cisco Controller' in new_data:
         break
```

