@zumoshi, thanks for the constant update. I have added a `TooManyRequestsError`. Telepot is now at version 6.8

Sorry to disappoint you again. I have decided *not* to include the original calling parameters in `TelegramError`. I'd like to keep them "clean" and not include things that are "bigger" than their immediate contexts. I have also referenced the [requests](http://docs.python-requests.org/en/master/api/#exceptions) library and [aiohttp](http://aiohttp.readthedocs.org/en/stable/api.html#module-aiohttp.errors) library and found that they tend to make the same choice, e.g. a [`HttpProcessingError`](http://aiohttp.readthedocs.org/en/stable/api.html#aiohttp.errors.HttpProcessingError) does not include the URL.

That said, I appreciate your efforts of helping me make telepot better. Feel free to make any more suggestions.

