@bacongobbler I'm honestly not sure at this point.  I'm strongly of the opinion that it needs to be easier to customize Deis clusters.  #2182 started with a few folks wanting it to be easier to install Deis without the storage subsystem.  I think it's easy enough to make something like that optional by means of an install wizard.  I think such an approach could easily take the pain out of all the most _common_ configuration options (log drains, etc.)

On the other hand, I get the sense that the level of customization that some people do is far more extensive and a framework for permitting such people to orchestrate the launch of Deis with their customizations seems like it would be a useful addition.  (My own use case is Deis with customized unit files and images - storage subsystem + monitoring stack.)

I think at this point I'm convinced that the latter has more value for myself, but I'm also interested in what provides the most value to the _community_.  Maybe there is room for both approaches?  Idk.  I'm really interested in hearing others sound off on this.

