@geigerj: gRPC is raising an exception with a non-public class, [but the public types of the instance that is raised are `grpc.RpcError` and `grpc.Call`](https://github.com/grpc/grpc/blob/9fec58f2b4727aae4c9368f3768cc1ef727bd523/src/python/grpcio/grpc/__init__.py#L452). Our intention is that application code be written something like
```
try:
    my_response = my_stub.MyMethod(my_request)
except grpc.RpcError as rpc_error:
    my_status_code = rpc_error.code()
    my_status_details = rpc_error.details()
    <statements taking action in response to the terminated RPC>
```
